<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100841009522234></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100841009522234><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6700&mid=100841009522234>simple, really</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6700&mid=100841009522234#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=89789><span id= >Essar</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>36 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 15th 4:54 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>the REASON we priests aren't sitting back medding is because if a mob is BEATING on us then we can't, and we need something to fend said mob off with since we don't get a pet (druid charms, which are useless, and shaman wolves, which are right next to that, being the exception), plus how many mobs are immune to being smacked?  Only clerics and necroes, and then only for a short while.  Plus it's fun to hit for 100+ with a priest, makes you feel all warm and squishy inside, especially since at about 15 we hit for maybe 15ish and the mobs hit US for 30-50...  <br><br>Plus, on the PoH raid we just did yesterday, I was main healer in a ranger group with my druid, and oh darn, they weren't taking any damage and I was FM...  was fun to brag to the rangers that I was hitting for high 30s with a druid while they were spamming away for mid 20s  8 )<br><br>Now I agree, that should this drop, monks and other melees are first for loots on this, as they ARE better at meleeing, but for Pete's sake, if the thing is rotting 'cause no one else wants it, you can bet my happy priest arse is looting it, and I have one of each priest class that would LOVE this little puppy about, oh, NOW.<br><br>Don't say the a priest is stupid for wielding this, EVER.  I would deal more damage with this and an FBSS than I would nuking with my druid and then medding the mana back.  Casters deal more damage in an instant than melees, but in the long run, even WE deal more damage in a long, drawn out fight, if our melee skills are high and we beat on it with a good weapon.  Trust me on this, I've done the math, I would deal more damage with this and an FBSS if I were to include the downtime from medding.  Plus we have situations like my PoH experience.<br><br>And of course, there is the occasion when we just don't feel like spending 250 mana to nuke that greenie goblin that just attacked us because we were sitting down...  it's just fun to kill those goblins again and go back to your newbie days when you still got exp for them and bit your gums cause you couldn't hit the stupid thing.<br><br>But what do I know, I just speak from experience and mathematical equations...<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
