	   <tr><td colspan=2>That's kinda goofy. Clerics 1HB skill is 4*(level + 1) while melee classes skill is 5 * (level +1). (Skill formulas changes after level 50 because they had to make skills for level 50 to 60 all be below 256 to fit in it's data field of 1 byte :). But by the time you are old enough to use this, your melee skills will pale in comparison (you'll hit about like a level 44 at level 55 - if that). Also, I there might be a cap on weapon skills for clerics before you even get that high!<br><br>Then you take into account the fact that you don't have double attack (or tripple attacks), dodge, parry, riposte, block, etc. and you have to ask yourself why you are wasting your time attempting to melee when you should be sitting down medding and using your nukes if you *really really* have to do damage.<br><br>This statment goes out to pretty much every post about non-melee classes envying over uber melee weapons that have no other advantage for the caster.<br>&nbsp;<br>Yuktii LifeStealer53<br>Necromancer of Quellious<br>Daaniel SilentWhisper - 34 Rogue</td></tr>
